columns.name: Borough
columns.description: On of the five borough of NYC: Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens, and Staten Island.

columns.name: NTAName
columns.description: Neighborhood Tabulation Area Name. Neighborhood Tabulation Areas are small area boundaries that were initially created by the Department of City Planning for small area population projections. However, NTAs are now being used to present data from the Decennial Census and American Community Survey.

columns.name: Zipcode
columns.description: Seven digit zip code of drop-off site

columns.name: SiteName
columns.description: Name of location where residents can drop off their electronics.

columns.name: SiteAddr
columns.description: Drop-off site street address

columns.name: HouseNum
columns.description: Drop-off site street address number

columns.name: DSNY District
columns.description: District abbreviation as defined by DSNY

columns.name: DSNY Section
columns.description: Sections are subdivisions of DSNY Districts

columns.name: DSNY Zone
columns.description: Zone abbreviation as defined by DSNY

columns.name: Community District
columns.description: Borough and Community District which is represented by a single-digit borough number followed by two-digit borough community district number.

columns.name: Census Tract
columns.description: Census Tract (CT2010). The 2010 census tract in which the tax lot is located.

columns.name: Council District
columns.description: NYC Council District Number. There are 51 Council districts throughout the five boroughs and each one is represented by an elected Council Member.

columns.name: Senate District
columns.description: New York City area State Senate District name.

columns.name: Congressional District
columns.description: New York City area Congressional District name.

columns.name: Assembly District
columns.description: New York City area Assembly District name.

columns.name: PolicePrec
columns.description: Police precinct in which the site is located.

columns.name: BIN
columns.description: Building Identification Number (BIN). A seven-digit numerical identifier unique to each building in the City of New York.

columns.name: BBL
columns.description: Ten digit Borough-Block-Lot (BBL) or parcel numbers identify the location of buildings or properties.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Latitude of drop-off site for mapping purposes

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Longitude of drop-off site for mapping purposes

columns.name: ObjectId
columns.description: An ObjectID is a unique, not null integer field used to uniquely identify rows in tables in a geodatabase.

columns.name: point
columns.description: Longitude and Latitude formatted for map "pin"

view.description: A list of locations where NYC residents can drop off unwanted electronics. It’s illegal in New York State to include electronic devices with trash or recycling. For more information on how to handle unwanted electronics in NYC, see: https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/dsny/site/services/electronics
